### Context Gathering

- [ ] Read the task file and its context header
- [ ] Read the service hub for this domain
- [ ] Read the design spec / screen spec
- [ ] Check contracts registry for required API endpoints
- [ ] Verify backend endpoints exist (test with curl/Postman)
- [ ] Check existing components catalog for reusable pieces

### Baseline Verification

- [ ] Run `{{TYPE_CHECK_CMD}}` to confirm clean baseline
- [ ] Run `{{LINT_CMD}}` to confirm no pre-existing lint errors
- [ ] Run `{{TEST_CMD}}` to confirm all tests pass before starting

### Specification Clarity

- [ ] Acceptance criteria are clear and testable
- [ ] Edge cases are identified (empty states, error states, permissions)
- [ ] Data model is understood (required fields, relationships, constraints)
- [ ] API request/response shapes are documented or agreed upon

### Dependencies

- [ ] No blocking dependencies unresolved
- [ ] Required backend endpoints exist OR are in the same sprint scope
- [ ] Required design tokens / components are available
- [ ] Auth roles and permissions are configured for this feature
- [ ] Third-party integrations are accessible (if applicable)

### Planning

- [ ] Component inventory listed (new vs. existing)
- [ ] File/folder structure planned (where new files will live)
- [ ] Estimated complexity: [ ] Small (< 2h) / [ ] Medium (2-6h) / [ ] Large (6h+)

